The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Stadium to be renovated next year

A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: The state government seems to have finally woken up to the sorry condition of the Salt Lake Stadium turf. It has sent a letter to the Indian Football Association (IFA), stating that February and April next year will be earmarked for renovation work. 

In this respect, the IFA has requested the AIFF to allow it to host next years NFL matches during that period at either Kanchenjungha Stadium, Siliguri or Barasat Stadium. 

Meanwhile, IMG World, the producer of Fifa Football Mundial, will telecast a half-hour show on Indian soccer. They will shoot footage of the April 24 East Bengal versus Mohun Bagan match at the Salt Lake Stadium with special focus on Bhaichung Bhutia, as well as on IFA?s Haldia Academy, informed IFA secretary Subrata Dutta. 

BASKETBALL: State league ties at WBBA courts from 3.30 pm. 

FOOTBALL: NFL: EB vs SBT (Salt Lake Stadium, 3.15 pm). 

HOCKEY: Beighton Cup qualifiers: Khalsa Blues AC vs Hockey Training Centre, Howrah (Mohammedan Sporting), CCFC Gremlins vs Police AC (CC amp;FC). Matches from 3.15 pm. 

TABLE TENNIS: Calcutta championship (CU Institute, 9.30 am). 

TENNIS: Age-group meet: Matches at Dalhousie Institute. 




